A Despatch man died when he was run down by a vehicle travelling on the R75 yesterday. Joseph Peta, 53, died when he apparently stepped in front of a VW Polo travelling towards Uitenhage. The accident happened shortly before 7am, police spokeswoman Captain Gerda Swart said. The man allegedly stepped off the verge into traffic. The driver of the Polo swerved to avoid him, but knocked him down, she said. Peta was declared dead on the scene. Swart said a case of culpable homicide would be investigated. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share